Thurston County is the second and final county reporting in WA-03 today. 320 votes counted, and Kent net gains 59 votes over JHB. Kent now in 2nd place by 928 votes.

Recounts are required in Washington when the margin between two candidates is less than 2,000 votes and less than 0.5%. Current margin between Kent and JHB is 869 votes and 0.4%.

Clark reports only 500 ballots remaining, and the other 6 counties combined report fewer than 1,000.

The 8,458 votes counted Tuesday in Clark County split Perez 34.3%, JHB 22.0%, Kent 20.9%.

There are fewer than 3k ballots remaining across all of WA-03.
